<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1419" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1419">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1410</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                            <gloss type="from">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MGT1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Marye</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>186. Your 19, January 14, and Department’s 127, January 30.<note n="2" xml:id="d1419fn2">See telegram of December 30, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_990">p. 990</ref>.</note> German
                            Ambassador here asks you transmit to Foreign Office request that German
                            prisoners now held in Astrakhan be liberated on ground they were taken
                            prisoners on neutral territory of neutral country and their detention
                            constitutes violation international law.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>